systems.
SB279 Enrolled
85 d. Existing paint on painted surfaces.
86 (10) Routine cleaning, waste disposal, and janitorial
87 services, including the cleaning, stripping, and waxing of
88 floors.
89 (b) The exemptions provided in subsection (a) shall
90 exclude a swimming pool contractor. Provided, however, a
91 person, firm, or corporation constructing a swimming pool on
92 his, her, or its own property shall be exempted from this
93 chapter.
94 (c)(b) A subcontractor, as defined in Section
95 34-8-1(c), is subject to and shall comply with this chapter as
96 specified for a general contractor except as follows:
97 (1) A subcontractor shall pay one-half of the fees
98 required in this chapter for a general contractor.
99 (2) No bid limits shall be established for a
100 subcontractor.
101 (3) A subcontractor shall submit with license
102 application and renewals a statement of financial condition as
103 prescribed by the board.
104 (4) A subcontractor shall furnish three references from
105 any combination of the following: Licensed general
106 contractors, registered professional engineers, or registered
107 architects, or qualified person, as declared by the board, for
108 whom they have worked. If a subcontractor has only been
109 employed by one company, the subcontractor shall provide the
110 following: Three or more jobs he or she has worked on, the
111 amounts of the contracts, the time period of the contracts,
112 the location of the contracts, and a statement of experience.
Page 4

the location of the contracts, and a statement of experience.
SB279 Enrolled
113 (5) A subcontractor is not required to be licensed at
114 the time a project is bid, but must be licensed with the board
115 prior to beginning work on the project.
116 (6) A general contractor license and license number
117 issued by the board to subcontractors shall denote
118 subcontractor status.
119 (7) A subcontractor is not required to sit for any
120 examination before being licensed."
121 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
122 1, 2026.
